َ","translation":"আল্লাহ","audioUrl":"wbw/005_087_015.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":66877,"position":15,"arabic":"لَا","translation":"না","audioUrl":"wbw/005_087_016.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":66878,"position":16,"arabic":"يُحِبُّ","translation":"ভালোবাসেন","audioUrl":"wbw/005_087_017.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":66879,"position":17,"arabic":"ٱلْمُعْتَدِينَ","translation":"সীমালঙ্ঘনকারীদেরকে","audioUrl":"wbw/005_087_018.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":66880,"position":18,"arabic":"٨٧","translation":"(৮৭)","audioUrl":null,"charTypeName":"end"}]},{"number":88,"arabic":"وَكُلُوا۟ مِمَّا رَزَقَكُمُ ٱللَّهُ حَلَٰلًۭا طَيِّبًۭا ۚ وَٱتَّقُوا۟ ٱللَّهَ ٱلَّذِىٓ أَنتُم بِهِۦ مُؤْمِنُونَ","translation":"Thus, partake of the lawful, good things which God grants you as sustenance, and be conscious of God, in whom you believe.","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/757.mp3","surahId":5,"words":[{"id":67244,"position":1,"arabic":"وَكُلُوا۟","translation":"এবং তোমরা খাও","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67245,"position":2,"arabic":"مِمَّا","translation":"তা হতে যা","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_002.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67246,"position":3,"arabic":"رَزَقَكُمُ","translation":"জীবিকা দিয়েছেন তোমাদের","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_003.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67247,"position":4,"arabic":"ٱللَّهُ","translation":"আল্লাহ","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_004.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67248,"position":5,"arabic":"حَلَـٰلًۭا","translation":"বৈধ","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_005.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67249,"position":6,"arabic":"طَيِّبًۭا ۚ","translation":"পবিত্র","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_006.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67251,"position":7,"arabic":"وَٱتَّقُوا۟","translation":"ও তোমরা ভয় করো","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_008.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67252,"position":8,"arabic":"ٱللَّهَ","translation":"আল্লাহকে","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_009.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67253,"position":9,"arabic":"ٱلَّذِىٓ","translation":"যিনি (মহান সত্ত্বা)","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_010.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67254,"position":10,"arabic":"أَنتُم","translation":"তোমরা","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_011.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67255,"position":11,"arabic":"بِهِۦ","translation":"উপর তাঁর","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_012.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67256,"position":12,"arabic":"مُؤْمِنُونَ","translation":"মু'মিন","audioUrl":"wbw/005_088_013.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67257,"position":13,"arabic":"٨٨","translation":"(৮৮)","audioUrl":null,"charTypeName":"end"}]},{"number":89,"arabic":"لَا يُؤَاخِذُكُمُ ٱللَّهُ بِٱللَّغْوِ فِىٓ أَيْمَٰنِكُمْ وَلَٰكِن يُؤَاخِذُكُم بِمَا عَقَّدتُّمُ ٱلْأَيْمَٰنَ ۖ فَكَفَّٰرَتُهُۥٓ إِطْعَامُ عَشَرَةِ مَسَٰكِينَ مِنْ أَوْسَطِ مَا تُطْعِمُونَ أَهْلِيكُمْ أَوْ كِسْوَتُهُمْ أَوْ تَحْرِيرُ رَقَبَةٍۢ ۖ فَمَن لَّمْ يَجِدْ فَصِيَامُ ثَلَٰثَةِ أَيَّامٍۢ ۚ ذَٰلِكَ كَفَّٰرَةُ أَيْمَٰنِكُمْ إِذَا حَلَفْتُمْ ۚ وَٱحْفَظُوٓا۟ أَيْمَٰنَكُمْ ۚ كَذَٰلِكَ يُبَيِّنُ ٱللَّهُ لَكُمْ ءَايَٰتِهِۦ لَعَلَّكُمْ تَشْكُرُونَ","translation":"GOD will not take you to task for oaths which you may have uttered without thought, but He will take you to task for oaths which you have sworn in earnest. Thus, the breaking of an oath must be atoned for by feeding ten needy persons with more or less the same food as you are wont to give to your own families, or by clothing them, or by freeing a human being from bondage; and he who has not the wherewithal shall fast for three days [instead]. This shall be the atonement for your oaths whenever you have sworn [and broken them]. But be mindful of your oaths!' Thus God makes clear unto you His messages, so that you might have cause to be grateful.","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/758.mp3","surahId":5,"words":[{"id":67674,"position":1,"arabic":"لَا","translation":"না","audioUrl":"wbw/005_089_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":67675,"position":2,"arabic":"يُؤَاخِذُكُمُ","translation":